# delay=0 fires immediately on tick 0. onlycoldstart=1 still fires here because
# the engine models every load as a cold start.
# SPEC-GAP: the engine has no warm-start (patch-reload) concept, so
# onlycoldstart's warm-start suppression is unobservable headlessly -- once
# always fires. Hardware/Rack reload state would be needed to exercise it.
tickrate 100
patch <<<
[once]
    delay         = 0
    onlycoldstart = 1
    trigger       = O1
>>>
@0 expect O1 1
@1 expect O1 0
@2 expect O1 0
